modules.description: This module generates cryptographically secure random values including integers, floating-point numbers, bytes, strings, and sequences. It supports data types like `int`, `int32`, `int64`, `float`, `char`, `bytes`, `string`, `Cstruct.t`, and `bigarray`, with functions to produce uniformly distributed values, bounded integers, and alphanumeric characters. It is used to create secure tokens, nonces, random identifiers, and test data with strong randomness guarantees.
